text: Mailiifterl is an Austrian niekname for the first computer working solely on transistors on the European mainland. It was built in 1955 at the Vienna University of Technology by Heinz Zemanek. The builder plays 011 a quote 0n an operating computer: If it is not the calculation speed of American models that Whirlwind or Typhoon can achieve; it will be enough for a Wiener Mailiifterl.
